    "scopeAndContentNote": "This series consists of audio recordings of interviews with U.S. Air Force personnel stationed at Roswell Air Force Base (later named Walker Air Force Base) as well as members of the Balloon Recovery Branch at Holloman Air Force Base, who discussed their experiences with high altitude balloon test flights in Roswell, New Mexico. In addition, Donald Schmitt, co-author of \"The Truth About the UFO Crash at Roswell\" is interviewed, as are alleged witnesses to events at Roswell Army Air Force (AAF) Hospital.",
    "naId": 566843,
    "functionAndUse": "These sound recordings were created or acquired in the process of investigating and gathering research materials to prepare the U.S. Air Force official publications, \"The Roswell Reports\" in 1994 and 1997. The reports examined alleged incidents of an unidentified flying object (UFO) crash at Roswell, New Mexico in July 1947.",
    "numberingNote": "Items are numbered from 1 to 18."
  }
